OL,3,CSix-time Olympic champion Sir Chris
OL,4,CHoy announces his cancer is terminal
OL,6,FSir Chris Hoy, one of Britain's
OL,7,Fgreatest cyclists and Olympians, has
OL,8,Frevealed that his cancer diagnosis is
OL,9,Fterminal.
OL,11,FThe former Team GB track cyclist says
OL,12,Fhe has been given two to four years to
OL,13,Flive.
OL,15,FThe 48-year-old announced in February
OL,16,Fthat he was undergoing treatment for
OL,17,Fan unspecified type of cancer and at
OL,18,Fthe time said he was "optimistic" and
OL,19,Fhis treatment was going "really well".
